replies.body:
{{champion:107}} 

I'd love to see more insight into Rengar's personality. I understand he's all proud, trophy hunter cat-man, but there's room for depth in there. What is he like when he's not stalking the jungles? How does he interact with people? For example - we know from Gnar's lore that Rengar keeps a hunting journal to jot down his thoughts and feelings during his hunts. Are they just for himself? Does he have any friends, or fellow hunters that he discusses tactics with and takes criticism from? Perhaps {{champion:76}} would be a good candidate for a person like that, someone Rengar can be bros with and talk about the nature of the hunt.

He also strikes me as a very proud person who'd love the opportunity to brag to people about his hunts. Does he go into towns with warriors and share tales of great hunts with them, or does he avoid civilization and it's comforts, subsisting completely in the wild? If so, where did his armor and weapons come from? These are all things updated dialogue could provide insight into.

{{champion:58}} 

An updated VO for Renekton would greatly depend on whether or not Riot is going to redeem him at any point. Will he overcome his madness and see the truth of what happened with his brother, or is he doomed to berserker rage for all eternity, until he's struck down? If he's redeemed, it would be cool to see how he feels about being Ascended, and dialogue on how it compares to him being a person would be neat. Can he even remember being a human before?

If he were redeemed, his rage towards Nasus would obviously be redirected towards Xerath, but it would be more sane, of course. If he isn't to be redeemed, and be written as a tragedy, it would be great to see some sorrow and a greater sense of betrayal under those scales.
